HEADWORD: Penitencer
<hw>Pen"i*ten*cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧nitencier</ets>.]</ety> <def>A priest who heard confession
and enjoined penance in extraordinary cases.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>penitenser</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
